<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#F0DCA0">Originally posted by Arhu on 08-22-2000 03:41 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Yep, pretty spiffy!  :]

And while I admire those drifting glamour lights.. will there be colored smoke somewhere or sometimes in  :div:? Not totally saturated ones, but slight, subtle shades. I imagine a park of mysterious hot springs and wells, or the premises of a herb woman's house, where potions and remedies of all kinds stand around, some of them vaporing, joss sticks everywhere... or the scenery of a firework or fair.. err, forget the latter; not really appropriate in times of war..  :(

Then I wonder: is there some indication for whether you're spell has worked or not? I mean, how can you know that you just turned fearless Otho into a scary Otho? Hm, dunno whether you should know at all, but the graphical effect of the Fear spell could depend on that.
If it worked, all the lights slowly fade away (as it currently seems to be), and if not, they and the skull flicker and "fall" to the ground or something, as if they were made of glass and have been broken (by the victim's resistence?).. Or something.

As for the mpg: supposed you use Xing and size does (not) matter, you could try to make a custom stream profile and set the system's data rate to 1998.00 (maximum), data rate to 1828 and audio rate to 128 (or data 1700, audio 256). Should/could provide even better quality...  ;)
Audio default is 112 or so, which is noticeably worse than 128. The mpg gets a little larger, though. But if the quality depends mostly on the grabber anyway... well, never mind.

[i]Meow...[/i]
Arhu</TEXTAREA>
